This paper deals with image representation learning for facial images, specifically for preserving head pose information while replacing the identity. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a novel variational generative adversarial network (VGAN) based on Wasserstein loss, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of this network in privacy-sensitive scenarios, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the synthesis of realistic face images, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
